title: Textile, 1851–63
medium:
Medium: cotton
Technique: printed by engraved roller and block printed; partially glazed
description: Ground printed in grey in an elaborate foliage pattern, probably by "molette". Over-printed in pattern of rose clusters in shades of brownish-red, lighter red; white areas in flowers glazed. Remains of a label, giving colors.
